    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc.02082.001_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <note type="editorial" place="top" resp="#ht">see notes Dec. 3, '90</note>
                    <handShift rend="printed"/>
                    <name type="place">OFFICE OF</name>
                    <name type="place">THE ARENA PUBLISHING</name>
                    <name type="place">EXPONENT OF MODERN THOUGHT</name>
                    <name type="place">EDITED BY B.O. FLOWER</name>
                    <name type="place">PER.ANNUM &#36;5</name>
                    <name type="place">SINGLE COPIES .50</name>
                    <name type="place">PIERCE BLD'G COPLEY SQ.</name>
                    <name type="place">BOSTON.</name>
                    <date when="1891-12-02"><handShift rend="manuscript"/>Dec. 2 <handShift rend="printed"/>189<handShift rend="manuscript"/>0.</date>
                </dateline> 
                <salute>Walt Whitman,</salute>
                <salute>Camden, NJ.</salute>
                <salute>My dear Sir:</salute>
            </opener>
            <p>Your esteemed favor containing poems submitted for the Arena received;&#8212;and in reply would say that
                I do not find the poems available at the present time. I should much prefer an essay from your pen
                to poems, as at the present time I have all the poems I can possibly use for some time to come.</p>
            <closer> 
                <salute>Cordially yours,</salute>
                <signed>B.O. <hi rend="underline">Flower</hi></signed>
            </closer>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc.02082.002_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
         </body>
